28/11/2002
PODGORICA, Montenegro, Yugoslavia -- The ruling Democratic Party of Socialists (DPS) has decided to nominate its deputy head Filip Vujanovic in the 22 December presidential elections. 
Party spokesman Igor Luksic says party leaders made the decision Wednesday (27 November), and will make it official during Friday's presidency session. 
In addition to his role in Milo Djukanovic's party, Vujanovic is parliament speaker and the acting president of the republic. 
DPS also decided to nominate another deputy party leader, Svetozar Marovic, as the presidential nominee in the future Yugoslav federation. 
(Tanjug, Montenegrin Mina, BBC - 27/11/02)
